Name: gynecomastia
Definition: A sex development disorder that is characterized by enlargement or swelling of male breast tissue resulting from elevated male estrogen levels or imbalanced estrogen and testosterone levels.

Name: hermaphroditism
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by deficiency of cytochrome c oxidase

Name: pseudohermaphroditism
Definition: An autosomal dominant disease that is characterized by the association of diffuse mesangial sclerosis (DMS)

Name: freemartinism
Definition: A kyphosis that results_in abnormal formation located_in body of vertebra.

Name: androgen insensitivity syndrome
Definition: A sex differentiation disease that is characterized by the partial or complete inability of the cell to respond to androgens in individuals with a karyotype of 46
